  "texts": [
    "MKOuldkhaoua et al. [71] reported a 16% increase in compressive strength after 90 days with a 10% MK replacement.",
    "Singh and Murugan [73] found significant improvements in compressive, split tensile, and flexural strengths at MK levels between 0 and 20%, with 15% being the most effective.",
    "Other studies support these findings, such as Zhan et al. [74] who observed a 42.30% increase in compressive strength with 10% MK.",
    "However, Jiang et al. [72] noted that while MK generally boosts strength, the benefits can vary with dosage and curing conditions.",
    "Kocak et al. [75] also indicated Vol."
  ]
}